lines.text: Mount Sinai Academic Family Health Team - Vaughan Site
Re: MAYA ROMANO #805964225 Sep 8, 1990 Age: 35 yr
1 RUNNYMEDE ROAD, TORONTO M652Y1 ON 8004 622 430 MH
Please see this pleasant 33 year old lady regarding ?hormonally driven facial
ash. Several times per year, she gets a burning blotchy red rash on both
cheeks (malar distribution), usually occurring around menses. This rash has
been evaluated multiple times by Dermatology, Allergy and Rheumatology (due
to positive ANA), without a cause being identified. It is not responsive to
steroids or other topical treatments. Pt has not been on OCP in a long time due
to side effects, and recent pregnancy (currently 8 months post partum). The
rash recently recurred. Is it possible it is being driven by progesterone levels?
